<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Isocoma</i> <i>menziesii</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the shrub canopy with <i>Artemisia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Baccharis</i> <i>sarothroides</i>, <i>Coreopsis</i> <i>gigantea</i>, <i>Gutierrezia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Lotus</i> <i>dendroideus</i>, <i>Lupinus</i> <i>albifrons</i> and <i>Salicornia</i> <i>depressa</i>. Herbs commonly present include <i>Astragalus</i> <i>miguelensis</i>, <i>Atriplex</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Bromus</i> <i>diandrus</i>, <i>Calystegia</i> <i>macrostegia</i>, <i>Carpobrotus</i> <i>chilensis</i>, <i>Cirsium</i> <i>occidentale</i>, <i>Distichlis</i> <i>spicata</i>, <i>Dudleya</i> <i>greenei</i> and <i>Nassella</i> <i>pulchra</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Shrubs < 1 m; cover is open to intermittent. Herbaceous layer is open to continuous, diverse, and grassy. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Isocoma menziesii</i> > 50% relative cover in the shrub canopy (Evens and San 2005).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Alluvial fans, arroyos, and stream terraces. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Isocoma menziesii</i> as a FACW* plant. </div>
</div>

        
