<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Isocoma menziesii </i>is a widespread and variable perennial with a woody caudex or low shrub. The species grows in central and southern California in arroyos, headlands, hillsides, and sand dunes. Five varieties make up this morphologically variable species (Nesom 2006). <br/>
<br/>
<i>Isocoma menziesii </i>typically occupies sandy soils and forms stands mixed with herbs and grasses. Most of these stands are the result of recent or frequent disturbance from several causes including fire, flooding, erosion, and human-caused clearing. In southern California, persistent stands that are composed usually of low matlike plants typically occur on sea bluffs and terraces. They may contain halophytes such as <i>Atriplex californica </i>and <i>Cressa truxillensis</i>. The relation of this alliance with <i>Hazardia squarrosa </i>and the <i>Lupinus chamissonis</i>- <i>Ericameria ericoides </i>alliances requires more sampling. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
