    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Southern California Coast</b> (261Bc, Be-f, Bh). Stands occur on coastal hills of San Diego Co. (Evens and San 2005) and on bluffs and mesas on Anacapa, Santa Cruz, San Miguel, Santa Rosa, Santa Catalina, and San Nicolas islands (Halverson et al. 1996, Johnson and Rodriguez 2001, Junak et al. 2007, Rodriguez et al. 2017).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Mountains and Valleys</b> (M262Bf, Bk, Bn). Stands exist in San Diego (Evens and San 2005) and western Riverside Cos. (Bramlet 1994).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
